Package UserInterface

Class UITextInputField

java.lang.Object
UserInterface.Frame
UserInterface.DocumentCell
UserInterface.UITextInputField
Direct Known Subclasses:
AddressBar
public class UITextInputField
extends DocumentCell
A class to represent a graphical element in which the user can provide keyboard input and navigate to the entered URL.

This input field displays a cursor and the usual text navigation actions such as moving the cursor and selecting text are supported.

    • handleKey

      public void handleKey​(int id, int keyCode, char keyChar, int modifiersEx)
      Handle key presses. This method does the right action when a key is pressed.
      • If the addressBar has no focus, it does nothing.
      • Else, if a key is clicked, it looks at what key it is and does the corresponding action.
      Overrides:
      handleKey in class Frame
      Parameters:

      keyCode - : The KeyEvent code (Determines the involved key)
      keyChar - : The character representation of the involved key
      modifiersEx - : Specifies other keys that were involved in the event
